author: wtopstaff
title: Jacksonville cruises past Stetson 41-14
text:
By The Associated Press October 10, 2015 9:34 pm 
JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) — Kade Bell threw five touchdown passes and Jacksonville cruised past Stetson 41-14 on Saturday. 
Bell was 23 of 40 for 247 yards and threw touchdown passes to five different receivers. He connected with Orlando Thomas and Damien Strange, both on 4-yarders, in the first quarter. Bell found Andy Jones from 10 yards in the second, Austin Leach from 15 in the third, and Austin Lawrence on a 21-yard score in the fourth. 
Armani Sampson intercepted a Ryan Tentler pass just before halftime and took it 46 yards for a touchdown. Jacksonville (5-0, 3-0 Pioneer) had four picks on the day, two by Dallas Jackson. 
Ulysses Bryant has 95 yards on 22 carries. Leach had four catches for 70 yards. 
For Stetson (1-4, 0-3), Tentler finished 13 of 30 for 111 yards, a touchdown pass and two interceptions. Colin McGovern was 7 of 15 for 118 yards and two picks. Topics:
